Package: upnews
Type: Package
Title: Display news for outdated GitHub packages
Version: 0.1.1
Date: 2018-10-20
Author: c(person("Aurelien", "Ginolhac", , "ginolhac@gmail.com", c("aut", "cre")))
Maintainer: Aurelien Ginolhac <ginolhac@gmail.com>
Description: This add-in will fetch the remote HEAD sha1 of local github packages 
    and compare them, to the remote HEAD (same branch). 
    If some packages are outdated, fetch and display a link to a NEWS file (case insensitive NEWS.md).
Depends: R (>= 3.2.5)
Imports:
  pbapply,
  gh
Suggests:
    DT,
    remotes,
    shinycssloaders,
    shiny (>= 0.13),
    miniUI (>= 0.1.1),
    rstudioapi (>= 0.5),
    testthat,
    covr
Enhances:
  tibble
License: Apache License (>= 2.0)
URL: https://github.com/ginolhac/upnews
BugReports: https://github.com/ginolhac/upnews/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
